The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Calcutta: The Melbourne Cricket Club (MCC) clarified on Sunday that the crowd attendance for Day I of the Boxing Day Test between Australia and England was 84, 345, 12,000 short of the actual capacity.     
	In a statement, released on Sunday, MCC said: The variance against actual attendance is 12,000 of which approximately 6000 is attributed to the MCC Members Reserve and 6,000 attributed to public/corporate/AFL members        
	Mumbai: Sachin Tendulkar will be felicitated by the Mumbais civic body once he returns from the ongoing tour of South Africa.         
	Berlin: Werder Bremen striker Hugo Almeida will join Turkish club Besiktas, the Bundesliga club said. Portugal international Almeidas contract with Werder was running out at the end of the season and the Germans opted to sell the 26-year-old now to cash in on a transfer fee.A contract extension was not possible. Receiving a fee through his transfer was the best option for Werder, club managing director Klaus Allofs said.            
	Bangkok: Bryan Robson put on a brave face on Sunday in explaining why he was clinging on to his job as Thailand coach after overseeing the countrys worst performances in recent years.         
	Calcutta: East Bengal players had a heated exchange with the referee during their U-19 Calcutta Football League match, against Bardhaman, that ended in a 2-2 draw on Sunday. The Tarun Dey-coached side were trailing by two goals before making up for the deficit to share the spoils.                                                                                                                                                       
